      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "TCF-USA's operational model is built on extreme cost-effectiveness and transparency. With a <cite id=\"15\">fundraising efficiency of $0.09 per $1 raised</cite>, the organization minimizes overhead to maximize classroom impact. Their governance is robust, featuring an <cite id=\"16\">independent board of 15 members</cite> and a <cite id=\"17\">100% score for Culture and Leadership</cite> from Charity Navigator. This institutional maturity allows them to manage large-scale grants, including <cite id=\"18\">$52,989,235 in total foreign grants</cite> distributed to implementing partners in Pakistan."
      ],
      "summary": "The Citizens Foundation USA (TCF-USA) is a premier educational nonprofit dedicated to <cite id=\"1\">building civil society in Pakistan</cite> by providing high-quality education to underprivileged children. Since its <cite id=\"2\">founding in 1995</cite>, the organization has established a massive footprint, providing <cite id=\"3\">operational support for 534 schools</cite> and facilitating the <cite id=\"4\">construction of 17 new school units</cite> in the most recent reporting period. TCF-USA operates with exceptional financial efficiency, reporting <cite id=\"5\">Total Revenue of $18,303,365</cite> with a <cite id=\"6\">program expense ratio of 89.5%</cite>, ensuring that nearly every dollar donated reaches the classroom. The organization is a <cite id=\"7\">verified zakat-eligible charity</cite>, specifically serving the <cite id=\"8\">fuqara (poor) and masakin (needy)</cite> through its educational programs. Beyond basic schooling, TCF-USA invests in long-term student success, providing <cite id=\"9\">133,000 higher education scholarships</cite> to help alumni transition into professional careers. Their commitment to sustainability is further evidenced by infrastructure improvements, such as <cite id=\"10\">converting 8 schools to solar energy</cite> to reduce long-term utility costs and environmental impact.",
